The paper presents a neural architecture for learning and refining structural correspondences between graphs, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of graph neural networks and message passing networks suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), while the applications in computer vision and entity alignment between knowledge graphs suggest a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and databases (cs.DB).
